# External Link Rules for City Pages

## Rental portal links — use root URLs only

Never link to filtered search results, city-scoped pages, or paginated URLs.
Always use the stable homepage root.

```
// ❌ BAD — deep search result URL
{ "url": "https://www.idealista.com/en/alquiler-viviendas/valencia-provincia/" }

// ✅ GOOD — stable root
{ "url": "https://www.idealista.com" }
```

## Facebook — never link, always plain text

Facebook search-result and group URLs are unstable or require login.
Use plain text guidance instead.

```
// ❌ BAD
{ "label": "Expat group", "url": "https://www.facebook.com/groups/..." }

// ✅ GOOD — text only, no url field
{ "label": "Search on Facebook: 'Valencia Expats' — many direct landlord deals" }
```

## When no stable city page exists

Use the platform root and add a short search hint in the label.

```
// ✅ GOOD
{ "label": "DDproperty.com — search 'Chiang Mai'", "url": "https://www.ddproperty.com" }
```

## searchPortalsIntro — add a search hint when portals need it

If portals don't have a city-specific stable URL, add one line to `searchPortalsIntro`:

```json
"searchPortalsIntro": [
  "These are local rental platforms — search your city name inside each one.",
  "Tip: arrive on a short-stay first — long-term deals are easier to find in person."
]
```

## Applies to

- `data/cities.json` — all `searchPortals[].url` fields
- `data/countries.json` — any `officialLink.url` fields
- Any future city pages added to the data layer
